nt-loan%20debt%20as%20a%20single%20mother.%20But%20this%20year%2C%20I%20turned%2053%20and%20my%20%24200%2C000%20loans%20were%20forgiven.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221774%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22close%20up%20of%20a%20website%20that%20reads%20%26quot%3Bstudent%20baking%26quot%3B%20and%20loans%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6528176e6561dd877e790e80%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221338%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3Enull%3Cp%3ESean%20Gladwell%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAfter%20I%20became%20a%20mom%20of%20five%20kids%2C%20I%20couldn't%20afford%20my%20student-loan%20repayments.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThis%20year%2C%20my%20%24200%2C000%20student%20debt%20was%20forgiven.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EI'm%20now%20able%20to%20think%20about%20my%20future%20and%20buy%20a%20house%20for%20my%20family.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Linda%20Whitman.%20It%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%201987%20when%20I%20started%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fstudent-loan-repayments-cant-buy-home-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecollege%20journey%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20Adams%20State%20College%20%E2%80%94%20now%20Adams%20State%20University%20%E2%80%94%20in%20Alamosa%2C%20Colorado.%20I%20was%2017%20and%20dreamed%20of%20becoming%20a%20high-school%20counselor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20one%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftaking-a-semester-off-college-student-yale-burnout-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esemester%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20some%20life%20events%20prevented%20me%20from%20studying%20full%20time%20until%201992.%20I%20graduated%20in%20May%201995%20with%20my%20bachelor's%20in%20psychology%20and%20started%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-recent-college-grads-get-work-ready-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egraduate%3C%2Fa%3E%20work%20in%20counseling.%20Life%20circumstances%20struck%20again%2C%20and%20I'm%20still%20five%20classes%20short%20of%20getting%20that%20graduate%20degree.%20I%20eventually%20changed%20direction%20and%20went%20into%20construction%20management%20%E2%80%94%20the%20field%20I've%20worked%20in%20for%20nearly%2022%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202009%2C%20I%20applied%20for%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstudentaid.gov%2Fmanage-loans%2Frepayment%2Fplans%2Fincome-driven%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eincome-driven%20repayment%20plan%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20was%20created%20under%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnche.ed.gov%2Flegislation%2Fcollege-cost-reduction-and-access%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520College%2520Cost%2520Reduction%2520and%2Cpurposes%2520of%2520federal%2520financial%2520aid.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ECollege%20Cost%20Reduction%20and%20Access%20Act%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%202007%20to%20make%20education%20more%20affordable%2C%20but%20it%20was%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstudentaid.gov%2Fannouncements-events%2Fidr-account-adjustment%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eone-time%20adjustment%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20resulted%20in%20my%20full%20loan%20forgiveness%20in%20August%20at%20age%2053.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHardships%20made%20it%20difficult%20to%20make%20student-loan%20payments%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20in%20a%20bad%20car%20accident%20in%20fall%201996%2C%20which%20gave%20me%20brain%20trauma.%20I%20tried%20one%20more%20semester%20of%20school%2C%20but%20I%20had%20to%20leave%20the%20counseling%20program.%20What%20I%20borrowed%20between%20my%20undergraduate%20and%20graduate%20work%20was%20about%20%2460%2C000%2C%20and%20it%20ballooned%20to%20more%20than%20%24200%2C000%20because%20of%20the%20compound%20interest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20my%20now-ex-husband%20went%20to%20prison%2C%20I%20became%20a%20single%20mom%20to%20five%20kids.%20I%20moved%20to%20Washington%20%E2%80%94%20to%20an%20island%20that%20doesn't%20have%20a%20whole%20lot%20of%20high-paying%20jobs.%20The%20first%20opportunity%20I%20got%20was%20working%20in%20a%20kitchen%2C%20and%20I%20then%20got%20an%20offer%20to%20go%20into%20construction%20and%20work%20at%20the%20office%20front%20desk.%20I%20did%20everything%20I%20could.%20I%20was%20working%2040%20hours%20a%20week%20at%20%2413%20an%20hour%2C%20which%20eventually%20increased%20to%20%2416.50%20an%20hour.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20awful.%20I%20wanted%20to%20pay%20my%20student%20loans%2C%20but%20it%20was%20more%20important%20to%20provide%20for%20my%20family.%20Even%20with%20state%20assistance%20%E2%80%94%20including%20food%20stamps%20and%20insurance%20%E2%80%94%20there%20wasn't%20enough%20money.%20I%20reconsolidated%20my%20loans%20twice%20so%20I%20could%20continue%20deferring%20them.%20I%20couldn't%20deal%20with%20it%2C%20so%20I%20didn't.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMy%20student%20loans%20were%20finally%20forgiven%20under%20the%20Biden%20administration%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20July%2C%20I%20received%20an%20email%20from%20the%20Education%20Department%20saying%20I%20was%20eligible%20to%20have%20my%20loans%20forgiven.%20The%20Biden%20administration%20granted%20a%20one-time%20adjustment%20for%20everyone%20who%20owed%20student%20debt%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ed.gov%2Fnews%2Fpress-releases%2Fbiden-harris-administration-begins-discharges-804000-borrowers-39-billion-automatic-loan-forgiveness-result-fixes-income-driven-repayment-plans%23%3A~%3Atext%3DBorrowers%2520are%2520eligible%2520for%2520forgiveness%2Cdischarged%2520over%2520the%2520coming%2520weeks.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Efor%2020%20to%2025%20years%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20forgiveness%20wasn't%20sudden.%20My%20debt%20on%20August%201%20was%20%24201%2C324.52.%20Now%2C%20granted%2C%20I%20didn't%20borrow%20that%20much%3B%20that%20number%20is%20thanks%20to%20interest.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20August%2014%2C%20I%20looked%20again%20and%20found%20that%20over%20%2488%2C000%20had%20been%20forgiven.%20It%20was%20the%20undergraduate%20portion.%20I%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BOh%2C%20thank%20you%2C%20Lord.%26quot%3B%20That%20was%20awesome.%20It%20cut%20my%20loans%20almost%20in%20half.%20This%20was%20a%20huge%20blessing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20end%20of%20August%2C%20I%20figured%20I%20needed%20to%20find%20out%20what%20my%20new%20payment%20would%20be%20come%20October.%20I%20looked%2C%20and%20it%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BPaid%20in%20full.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20balance%20was%20zero.%20I%20just%20screamed%20in%20shock.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMy%20life%20has%20changed%20after%20student-loan%20forgiveness%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20posted%20on%20Facebook%20to%20thank%20every%20taxpayer%20for%20contributing%20to%20my%20loan%20forgiveness%2C%20and%20some%20of%20the%20comments%20from%20my%20%26quot%3Bfriends%26quot%3B%20were%20saddening.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTell%20me%20how%20that%20is%20fair.%20No%20one%20is%20helping%20me%20pay%20off%20my%20mortgage%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20person%20commented.%20Another%20wrote%2C%20%26quot%3BHere's%20a%20thought%E2%80%A6Pay%20your%20loans%20back%20yourself.%20Be%20responsible%20for%20yourself!%20If%20you%20can't%20afford%20to%20pay%20back%20a%20loan%20don't%20borrow%20the%20money.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20I%20sit%20in%20my%20excitement%20now%20with%20just%20a%20few%20close%20family%20members.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'd%20been%20trying%20for%20the%20past%20seven%20or%20eight%20years%20to%20buy%20a%20house%2C%20but%20my%20loans%20were%20stopping%20me.%20Now%20I%20will%20finally%20be%20able%20to%20do%20that%2C%20and%20I'm%20so%20excited.%20I%20had%20been%20feeling%20like%20I'd%20failed%20to%20achieve%20the%20American%20dream%20of%20owning%20a%20home.%20However%2C%20when%20I%20saw%20my%20student-loan%20statement%20say%2C%20%2