s%20to%20being%20a%20detective%2C%20and%20touted%20his%20short%20seller's%20eye.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3ECombs%20is%20one%20of%20Warren%20Buffett's%20two%20investment%20managers%20at%20Berkshire%20Hathaway.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ETodd%20Combs%20spoke%20about%20his%20mother's%20sky-high%20expectations%2C%20the%20importance%20of%20taking%20risks%2C%20and%20the%20need%20for%20intense%20passion%20and%20ambition%20to%20achieve%20excellence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECombs%20helps%20Warren%20Buffett%20manage%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fstocks%2Fbrk-b-stock%5C%22%3EBerkshire%20Hathaway%3C%2Fa%3E's%20vast%20portfolio%20of%20stocks%20and%20other%20investments%2C%20and%20serves%20as%20CEO%20of%20Berkshire-owned%20Geico.%20He%20compared%20digging%20into%20a%20company%20to%20detective%20work%2C%20and%20underlined%20the%20value%20of%20having%20a%20short%20seller's%20eye%20when%20analyzing%20businesses.%20He%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fwarren-buffett-charlie-munger-todd-combs-stocks-portfolio-manager-berkshire-2023-10%5C%22%3Emade%20the%20comments%3C%2Fa%3E%20during%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.joincolossus.com%2Fepisodes%2F14034172%2Fcombs-todd-combs-investing-the-last-liberal-art%3Ftab%3Dtranscript%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecent%20episode%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20%26quot%3BArt%20of%20Investing%26quot%3B%20podcast.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHere%20are%20Combs'%208%20best%20quotes%2C%20lightly%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity%3A%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E1.%20%26quot%3BMy%20mother%20could%20have%20been%20a%20CEO%20in%20her%20own%20right.%20She%20didn't%20go%20to%20college%20because%20she%20didn't%20have%20an%20opportunity%20back%20then.%20So%20I%20think%20she%20wanted%20to%20channel%20all%20those%20missed%20opportunities%20in%20her%20life%20into%20mine.%20I'll%20never%20forget%20coming%20home%20one%20time%20with%20an%20A-%2C%20and%20I%20think%20I%20got%20grounded%20and%20all%20kinds%20of%20stuff.%20So%20she%20was%20very%2C%20very%20militant.%20She%20was%20the%20original%20tiger%20mom.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E2.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20super%2C%20super%20important%20to%20take%20a%20lot%20of%20risk%20when%20you're%20young.%20You've%20got%20nothing%20to%20lose%20at%20your%20age%2C%20you%20take%20the%20risk%20and%20you%20can%20massively%20screw%20up%2C%20and%20nobody's%20going%20to%20really%20hold%20it%20against%20you%20unless%20it's%20fraud%20or%20something%20like%20that.%20Take%20intelligent%20risk%2C%20don't%20take%20stupid%20risk.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E3.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20do%20you%20do%20with%20a%20jigsaw%20puzzle%3F%20You%20dump%20out%20all%20the%20pieces%20and%20you%20start%20with%20the%20edges%20and%20the%20corners.%20You%20don't%20start%20in%20the%20middle%20and%20build%20your%20way%20out.%26quot%3B%20(Exploring%20different%20fields%20and%20taking%20risks%20is%20a%20great%20way%20to%20make%20your%20mistakes%20early%20and%20find%20your%20passion%2C%20Combs%20said.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E4.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20usually%20rise%20to%20their%20level%20of%20complacency.%20If%20your%20dream%20is%20to%20make%20it%20to%20manager%20and%20you're%20perfectly%20fine%20there%2C%20that's%20pretty%20much%20where%20you're%20going%20to%20stop.%20That%20doesn't%20mean%20if%20you've%20got%2010%2C000%20people%20who%20all%20want%20to%20be%20CEO%20or%20whatever%20that%20they're%20all%20going%20to%20achieve%20it%2C%20but%20people%20create%20their%20own%20limiting%20factors.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E5.%20%26quot%3BI%20have%20never%20really%20been%20ready%20for%20anything%20in%20my%20life.%20When%20people%20see%20things%20in%20you%20that%20you%20don't%20see%20in%20yourself%2C%20that's%20amazing.%20And%20that%20was%20true%20with%20Steve.%20That%20was%20certainly%20true%20with%20Charlie.%20That%20was%20true%20with%20Warren%2C%20multiple%20times%20with%20Warren%20for%20Berkshire.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E6.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20like%20the%20detective%20that%20could%20show%20them%20the%20map%20and%20the%20terrain%20and%20tear%20it%20all%20apart.%20I'm%20like%2C%20'Oh%2C%20yes%2C%20this%20is%20a%20total%20fraud%2C'%20and%20I'm%20triangulating%20all%20this%20stuff%2C%20putting%20the%20puzzle%20pieces%20together.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E7.%20%26quot%3BShort%20selling%20is%20no%20different%20than%20long%20investing%20in%20my%20humble%20opinion.%20Very%2C%20very%2C%20very%20few%20people%20know%20what%20they're%20doing%2C%20it's%20very%20hard.%20You%20don't%20have%20a%20primary%20care%20physician%20go%20do%20brain%20surgery.%20I%20always%20felt%20you%20had%20to%20be%20about%2080%25%2C%2085%25%20correct%20on%20the%20short%20side%20to%20make%20money.%20You%20have%20to%20be%20damn%2C%20damn%20good%2C%20but%20that%20helps%20you%20on%20the%20long%20side%20if%20you%20don't%20become%20myopic%20or%20dogmatic%20or%20solve%20for%20the%20lazy%20narrative%20or%20any%20of%20that%20stuff.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%20(Berkshire%20doesn't%20short%20but%20Combs%20finds%20his%20short-selling%20skills%20help%20him%20identify%20companies'%20weaknesses.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E8.%20%26quot%3BThere's%201%20million%20people%20that%20want%20to%20be%20Djokovic%2C%20or%20Tom%20Brady%2C%20or%20Steph%20Curry%2C%20or%20Warren%20Buffett.%20Grit%20and%20pushing%20yourself%20can%20go%20a%20long%20way.%20But%20in%20a%20world%20where%201%20million%20people%20are%20trying%20to%20do%20this%2C%20if%200.1%25%20of%20them%20just%20absolutely%20love%20it%20so%20passionately%20that%20they're%20going%20to%20bed%20thinking%20about%20it%2C%20they're%20waking%20up%20thinking%20about%20it%2C%20you're%20never%20going%20to%20be%20able%20to%20compete%20with%20that%20if%20you%20don't%20love%20it%20to%20your%20core.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwarren-buffett-todd-combs-berkshire-hathaway-quotes-short-selling-stocks-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2