ckleball%20Center.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Jon%20Neeter%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EFormer%20collegiate%20coach%20Jon%20Neeter%20bought%20a%20tennis%20center%20in%20Santa%20Monica%2C%20CA%20for%20%2440%2C000%20in%202010.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20ran%20a%20successful%20tennis%20business%20for%20years%2C%20barely%20survived%20the%20pandemic%2C%20and%20then%20pivoted%20to%20pickleball.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20converted%20his%20single%20tennis%20court%20into%20four%20pickleball%20courts%20and%20business%20is%20booming.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can%20find%20a%20little%20bit%20of%20everything%20on%20Wilshire%20Boulevard%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.latimes.com%2Fla-ca-wilshire-boulevard-los-angeles-index-dto-htmlstory.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eone%20of%20Los%20Angeles'%20longest%20and%20most%20prominent%20streets%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20apartment%20towers%20and%20office%20buildings%3B%20trendy%20restaurants%20and%20fast%20food%3B%20theaters%20and%20museums.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWilshire%20stretches%2016%20miles%2C%20from%20industrial%20Downtown%20LA%20to%20beachy%20Santa%20Monica%20%E2%80%94%20and%20on%20the%20Santa%20Monica%20side%20of%20the%20street%2C%20nestled%20between%20an%20urban%20park%20and%20an%20iPhone%20repair%20store%2C%20you'll%20find%20a%20single%20tennis%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUp%20until%20August%202023%2C%20the%20court%20and%20adjoining%20pro%20shop%20operated%2C%20as%20one%20would%20expect%2C%20as%20a%20tennis%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20family%20in%20town%20ran%20a%20tennis%20business%20for%20many%20years%20there%2C%20since%20the%2060s%20I%20believe%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20current%20owner%2C%20Jon%20Neeter%2C%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20he%20purchased%20it%20in%202010%2C%20it%20wasn't%20in%20the%20greatest%20shape.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20business%20at%20the%20time%20amounted%20to%20%26quot%3Bbasically%20a%20ball%20machine%2C%20two%20ball%20carts%2C%20four%20ball%20tubes%2C%20and%20no%20client%20list%20whatsoever%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Neeter%2C%20a%20New%20Jersey%20native%20who%20coached%20collegiate%20tennis%20at%20Duke%20University%20before%20moving%20to%20California%20in%202005.%20But%20he%20knew%20it%20had%20potential%20because%20of%20its%20location.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20have%2045%2C000%20cars%20driving%20by%20a%20day%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20many%20of%20which%20get%20stopped%20at%20the%20traffic%20light%20outside%20of%20the%20shop.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDrivers%20and%20passengers%20caught%20at%20a%20red%20light%2C%20or%20pedestrians%20strolling%20on%20Wilshire%2C%20can%20see%20the%20pro%20shop%20from%20the%20street%20%E2%80%94%20but%20the%20court%20itself%20isn't%20discernible%20until%20you%20actually%20walk%20inside%20and%20see%20the%20sliding%20door%20at%20the%20back%20of%20the%20shop%20that%20opens%20up%20to%20a%20single%2C%20fenced-in%20court.%20Discovering%20it%20is%20like%20stumbling%20into%20a%20speakeasy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EBuying%20the%20business%20in%202010%20for%20%2440%2C000%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20working%20as%20the%20head%20pro%20at%20the%20Palisades%20Tennis%20Center%20for%20a%20few%20years%2C%20Neeter%20transitioned%20to%20working%20for%20himself%2C%20coaching%20his%20own%20clients%20at%20public%20parks%20and%20backyard%20courts.%20That's%20what%20he%20was%20doing%20when%20the%20tennis%20shop%20on%20Wilshire%20was%20listed%20for%20sale.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20felt%20too%20good%20to%20pass%20up%2C%20considering%20the%20location.%20Plus%2C%20he%20liked%20the%20idea%20of%20his%20work%20being%20concentrated%20in%20one%20place%2C%20rather%20than%20scattered%20at%20various%20tennis%20courts%20all%20over%20LA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22jon%20neeter%20smtc%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6529ad4968f1d46f52b1bb20%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENeeter%2C%20right%2C%20coached%20collegiate%20tennis%20before%20moving%20to%20California%20in%202005.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Jon%20Neeter%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20didn't%20want%20to%20be%20a%20nomad%20forever%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Neeter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20and%20his%20business%20partner%20at%20the%20time%2C%20Jon%20Arend%2C%20immediately%20reached%20out%20to%20the%20seller.%20Their%20vision%20was%20to%20run%20a%20high-performance%20tennis%20academy%2C%20which%20Neeter%20would%20take%20the%20lead%20on%2C%20in%20tandem%20with%20an%20indoor%20gym%2C%20which%20Arend%2C%20an%20athletic%20trainer%2C%20would%20run.%20They%20would%20call%20it%20Court%20Strength.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20had%20a%20plan%20and%20they%20liked%20our%20plan%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Neeter%2C%20who%20assumes%20there%20were%20other%20interested%20buyers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20duo%20bought%20the%20business%20for%20%2440%2C000%20and%20borrowed%20private%20money%20to%20do%20so%2C%20he%20said.%20They%20were%20purchasing%20just%20the%20business%20%E2%80%94%20not%20the%20property.%20That%2C%20they%20had%20to%20rent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENeeter%20was%20hoping%20to%20lock%20in%20the%20longest%20lease%20possible%2C%20to%20give%20them%20time%20to%20create%20a%20profitable%20business%2C%20but%20the%20owner's%20eventual%20plan%20was%20to%20sell%20the%20property%20and%20would%20only%20agree%20to%20three%20years%20at%20a%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKnowing%20that%20the%20property%20owner%20eventually%20wanted%20to%20sell%20the%20land%20to%20a%20developer%2C%20which%20would%20leave%20Neeter%20without%20a%20space%20to%20operate%20his%20business%2C%20felt%20%26quot%3Buncomfortable%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20admitted.%20%26quot%3BI%20always%20felt%2C%20from%20the%20first%20lease%20we%20signed%20in%202010%2C%20that%20there%20was%20a%20ticking%20clock%20on%20the%20place.%26quot%3B%20He%20expected%20to%20have%20the%20space%20for%20six%20to%20nine%20years%20max%2C%20%26quot%3Bif%20I%20was%20lucky%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Neeter%2C%20who's%20still%20there%2013%20years%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20he%20chose%20to%20think%20of%20it%20all%20as%20a%20bit%20of%20an%20experiment%3A%20If%20he%20could%20make%20this%20single%20court%20profitable%2C%20he%20figured%20he%20could%20replicate%20his%20business%20model%20elsewhere%20if%20and%20when%20he%20couldn't%20renew%20his%20lease.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EBusiness%20pivots%3A%20From%20high-performance%20academy%20style%20to%20community-driven%20tennis%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENeeter%20had%20already%20been%20running%20a%20business%2C%20in%20a%20sense%2C%20when%20he%20was%20doing%20private%20coaching%2C%20which%20required%20building%20a%20client%20list%2C%20buying%20and%20providing%20equipment%2C%20and%20figuring%20out%20a%20pricing%20model.%20Plus%2C%20he'd%20been%20immersed%20in%20tennis%20operations%20at%20the%20Palisades%3A%20%26quot%3BThat's%20where%20I%20learned%20how%20to%20be%20very%2C%20very%20efficient%20with%20tennis%20courts%20in%20general.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20the%20early%20days%20of%20Court%20Strength%20was%20%26quot%3Bway%20more%20work%20than%20I%20thought%20%E2%80%94%20and%20I%20knew%20it%20was%20going%20to%20be%20a%20lot%20of%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Neeter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221953%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22jon%20neeter%20smtc%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6529adfa6561dd877e7aae93%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221459%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENeeter's%20business%20was%20initially%20called%20Court%20Strength.%20Tennis%20professionals%20like%20Sam%20Querrey%20(center)%20have%20trained%20on%20his%20court.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Jon%20Neeter%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20early%20challenges%20he%20faced%20was%20doing%20facility%20upgrades%2C%20like%20fixing%20the%20windscreens%20or%20installing%20new%20lights%2C%20while%20still%20keeping%20the%20court%20up%20and%20running.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20couldn't%20renovate%20when%20clients%20were%20on-court%20and%2C%20%26quot%3Bit's%20not%20like%20we%20had%20a%20second%20court%20to%20shut%20down%20and%20do%20one%20at%20a%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20He%20ended%20up%20doing%20the%20renovations%20before%20opening%20and%20after%20closing%2C%20which%20made%20for%20late%20nights%20and%20early%20mornings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20beginning%2C%20it%20was%20a%20lot%20of%2010-%2C%2011-hour%20days%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Neeter%2C%20who%20was%20also%20doing%20most%20of%20the%20on-court%20coaching.%20%26quot%3BI%20had%20a%20front%20desk%20person%20for%20certain%20hours%2C%20I%20outsourced%20things%20like%20racket%20stringing%2C%20and%20I%20would%20teach%20a%20lot%20of%20hours%20to%20the%20point%20where%20I%20ran%20myself%20into%20the%20ground.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20taking%20a%20salary%2C%20%26quot%3Bsort%20of%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20drew%20money%20on%20the%20lessons%20that%20I%20taught.%26quot%3B%20Besides%20that%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20wasn't%20taking%20a%20salary%20for%20many%20years.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThanks%20to%20a%20lean%20operation%2C%20Neeter%20says%20he%20was%20able%20to%20pay%20back%20the%20private%20loan%20he%20took%20to%20buy%20the%20place%20by%20the%20end%20of%20year%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20model%20of%20focusing%20on%20developing%20elite%2C%20high-performing%20junior%20players%20was%20working%20but%2C%20ultimately%2C%20it%20was%20too%20niche%20to%20sustain%20long-term.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERetaining%20top%20players%20is%20incredibly%20difficult%2C%20explained%20Neeter%3A%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20the%20most%20fickle%20part%20of%20the%20tennis%20world%3A%20Players%20come%20and%20go%20%E2%80%94%20and%20once%20one%20or%20two%20players%20go%2C%20then%20they%20all%20go%20somewhere%20else.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAround%202015%2C%20he%20decided%20to%20shift%20to%20all-around%20programming%20and%20community-driven%20tennis%2C%20rather%20than%20exclusively%20focusing%20on%20high-performance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20changed%20the%20company%20name%20to%20the%20Santa%20Monica%20Tennis%20Center%20and%2C%20between%202015%20and%202019%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20business%20became%20really%20efficient%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere%20were%20days%20where%20the%20court%20would%20be%20busy%20from%207%20a.m.%20to%209%20p.m.%20at%20night%2C%20and%20if%20there%20was%20a%20half-hour%20to%20an%20hour%20empty%2C%20it%20was%20a%20bad%20day.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EBarely%20surviving%20Covid%20and%20pivoting%20once%20again%20%E2%80%94%20this%20time%2C%20to%20pickleball%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20years%20of%20being%20on%20%26quot%3Bcruise%20control%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Neeter%2C%202019%20tested%2C%20and%20almost%20broke%2C%20the%20small%20business%20owner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20particularly%20bad%20rainstorm%20in%20southern%20California%20destroyed%20the%20pro%20shop's%20roof%2C%20forcing%20Neeter%20to%20close%20doors%20in%20the%20summer%20of%202019.%20He%20could%20still%20offer%20lessons%20and%20clinics%20on-court%2C%20but%20retail%2C%20which%20had%20started%20to%20take%20off%2C%20was%20shut%20down%20temporarily%20as%20he%20went%20through%20the%20long%20and%20expensive%20process%20of%20rebuilding%20a%20roof.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20%26quot%3Bthe%20most%20challenging%2C%20stressful%20year%20of%20my%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Neeter.%20Until%20the%20coronavirus%20pandemic%20hit%2C%20that%20is.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22smtc%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6529afc468f1d46f52b1bec8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222268%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUntil%202022%2C%20Neeter's%20retail%20shop%20was%20330-square-feet.%20The%20shop%20opens%20up%20to%20a%20single%20tennis%20court%20that's%20fenced%20in%20and%20surrounded%20by%20palm%20trees.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Jon%20Neeter%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20reopening%20the%20shop%20in%20the%20fall%20of%202019%2C%20%26quot%3Ball%20of%20a%20sudden%20it%20was%20like%2C%20okay%2C%20now%20we%20can%20breathe%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20then%2C%202020.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20months%2C%20zero%20revenue%20came%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEverything%20was%20very%20strict%20in%20Santa%20Monica%2C%26quot%3B%20recalled%20Neeter%20of%20the%20early%20pandemic%20days.%20%26quot%3BThey%20took%20down%20the%20tennis%20nets%20at%20the%20public%20courts.%20They%20closed%20off%20the%20basketball%20hoops%2C%20put%20wood%20on%20top%20of%20the%20rims%2C%20at%20the%20public%20parks.%20Nobody%20could%20do%20anything.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20July%202020%2C%20as%20shops%20and%20businesses%20started%20to%20reopen%2C%20he%20started%20emailing%20clients%20to%20get%20a%20feel%20for%20what%20they%20would%20be%20comfortable%20participating%20in%20tennis-wise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20group%20classes%2C%20which%20were%20our%20bread%20and%20butter%2C%20didn't%20get%20going%20right%20away%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20more%20private%20stuff%2C%20which%20is%20not%20as%20lucrative.%20So%20we%20were%20running%20in%20the%20red%20for%20a%20while.%20We%20had%20rent%20relief%20from%20the%20state%20but%20that%20was%20just%20delayed%20rent.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20the%20PPP%20loans%2C%20they%20%26quot%3Bweren't%20that%20helpful%20for%20us%20because%20we%20had%20a%20small%20staff%20and%20some%20independent%20contractors%2C%26quot%3B%20added%20Neeter%2C%20who%20ended%20up%20taking%20an%20Economic%20Injury%20Disaster%20Loan%20(EIDL)%2C%20which%2C%20unlike%20a%20PPP%20loan%2C%20eventually%20has%20to%20be%20repaid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20loan%2C%20however%2C%20is%20%26quot%3Bwhat%20allowed%20us%20to%20continue%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BOtherwise%2C%20it%20wouldn't%20have%20worked.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETennis%20did%20become%20more%20popular%20in%20the%20aftermath%20of%20Covid%20with%20it%20being%20a%20socially%20distanced%20sport%2C%20which%20was%20reflected%20in%20Neeter's%20retail%20numbers%2C%20but%20there%20was%20a%20moment%20when%20he%20doubted%20a%20comeback%2C%20he%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20had%20lost%20a%20little%20bit%20of%20motivation%20in%20moving%20forward.%20Everything%20was%20uncertain%2C%20so%20why%20try%20so%20hard%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdding%20to%20the%20uncertainty%20of%20his%20business%2C%20in%202021%2C%20the%20property%20he%20leases%20sold%20to%20a%20developer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20like%2C%20'Okay%2C%20that's%20it.%20My%20lease%20is%20going%20to%20end%20and%20then%20I'm%20out%2C'%26quot%3B%20said%20Neeter.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20wound%20up%20happening%20due%20to%20construction%20complications%20in%20California%20and%20interest%20rates%20was%2C%20all%20these%20plans%20got%20delayed%20at%20least%20two%20years%2C%20if%20not%20three.%20It%20was%20great%20news%20for%20me.%20But%20now%20I%20still%20have%20to%20figure%20out%20what%20I'm%20going%20to%20do%20after%20this.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20initial%20plan%20of%20taking%20his%20business%20model%20to%20a%20new%20location%20didn't%20look%20like%20it%20was%20going%20to%20pan%20out%20when%20he%20realized%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20can't%20just%20move%20a%20tennis%20center%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20land%20doesn't%20work%20in%20West%20LA.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20tennis%20was%20growing%20in%20popularity%20post-pandemic%2C%20so%20was%20another%20racket%20sport%3A%20pickleball%2C%20which%20is%20played%20on%20a%20smaller%20court%20with%20a%20smaller%20paddle%20and%20a%20wiffleball.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22santa%20monica%20pickleball%20center%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6529b07e68f1d46f52b1bfaf%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20standard%20pickleball%20court%20is%2020%20feet%20wide%20by%2044%20feet%20long%2C%20much%20smaller%20than%20a%20tennis%20court.%20%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Jon%20Neeter%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20had%20been%20around%20for%20years%2C%20gradually%20gaining%20traction%2C%20explained%20Neeter%3A%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20not%20this%20explosive%20growth%20at%20first.%20It%20was%20more%20like%20a%20crawl%20pace.%20It%20started%20to%20get%20some%20legs%20in%202017%20but%20when%20the%20pandemic%20happened%2C%20that's%20when%20it%20really%20exploded%20because%20people%20could%20do%20it%20in%20their%20backyards%20and%20in%20their%20driveways%2C%20while%20everywhere%20else%20was%20closed.%20It%20gave%20people%20social%20outlets%20during%20a%20very%20difficult%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe'd%20been%20paying%20attention%20to%20pickleball%20throughout%20the%202010s%20but%20didn't%20necessarily%20know%20what%20to%20do%20with%20it%20%E2%80%94%20or%20even%20have%20much%20of%20an%20interest%20in%20it%20at%20that%20time.%20After%20all%2C%20until%202019%2C%20his%20tennis%20center%20was%20a%20well-oiled%20machine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20fall%20of%202022%2C%20Neeter%20saw%20first-hand%20just%20how%20big%20the%20game%20was%20getting.%20A%20friend%20told%20him%20to%20meet%20him%20at%20Santa%20Monica's%20Memorial%20Park%2C%20which%20had%20become%20a%20pickleball%20mecca%20in%20Southern%20California.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20were%20like%20200%20people%20on%20four%20tennis%20courts%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20recalled.%20%26quot%3BI%20couldn't%20find%20him%20on%20these%20four%20tennis%20courts.%20I'd%20never%20seen%20anything%20like%20it%20and%20was%20like%2C%20'Okay%2C%20I%20get%20it.%20This%20is%20a%20big%20thing.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHaving%20run%20a%20tennis%20center%20for%20over%20a%20decade%2C%20bringing%20a%20different%20racket%20sport%20to%20his%20shop%20and%20court%20wouldn't%20be%20easy%20or%20cheap.%20It%20would%20mean%20potentially%20losing%20the%20customer%20base%20he'd%20spent%20years%20building%20a%20relationship%20with%20and%20finding%20new%20suppliers%20for%20his%20retail%20shop%20%E2%80%94%20all%20for%20a%20sport%20with%20an%20unknown%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Neeter%20felt%20like%20he%20had%20nothing%20to%20lose%2C%20considering%20the%20uncertainty%20of%20his%20lease.%20Plus%2C%20he%20was%20unsure%20about%20how%20he%20was%20going%20to%20replicate%20the%20Santa%20Monica%20Tennis%20Center%20anywhere%20else%20in%20LA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20fall%20of%202022%2C%20he%20decided%20to%20go%20all-in%20on%20pickleball.%20He%20started%20by%20simply%20ordering%20paddles%20and%20adding%20them%20to%20his%20retail%20shop.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENext%2C%20he%20asked%20the%20developer%2C%20his%20new%20landlord%2C%20if%20he%20could%20lease%20the%20space%20next%20door%2C%20which%20they'd%20also%20acquired.%20His%20original%20pro%20shop%20space%20was%20small%2C%20about%20330%20square%20feet%2C%20and%20not%20big%20enough%20in%20his%20opinion%20to%20build%20a%20comprehensive%20pickleball%20retail%20store%2C%20which%20he%20has%20since%20done.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20people%20walk%20through%20the%20door%20we%20often%20get%20a%20'whoa'%20or%20a%20'wow%2C'%26quot%3B%20said%20Neeter%2C%20whose%20shop%20is%20now%202%2C000-square-feet.%20%26quot%3BThe%20intent%20was%20to%20impress%20people%20like%20that%20from%20the%20get%20go.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20got%20the%20keys%20to%20the%20second%20space%20in%20November%202022%20and%20hosted%20a%20grand%20opening%20in%20December.%20The%20turn-out%20was%20reaffirming%20in%20his%20decision%20to%20lean%20into%20pickleball.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20were%2050%20people%20waiting%20outside%20the%20door%20for%20us%20to%20open%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20recalled.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20crazy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221284%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22santa%20monica%20pickle%20ball%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6529b12255f52b01b35fa24a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221210%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20view%20from%20above%20at%20the%20Santa%20Monica%20Pickleball%20Center.%20Neeter%20fit%20four%20courts%20in%20the%20space%20that%20previously%20fit%20just%20one%20tennis%20court.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Jon%20Neeter%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPaddle%20sales%20have%20remained%20strong%20since%20opening%20day%2C%20which%20Neeter%20didn't%20necessarily%20expect%3A%20%26quot%3BRetail%20has%20done%20things%20I%20never%20thought%20it%20would.%20I%20knew%20it%20would%20be%20good%20but%20we're%20talking%20about%20having%20six-figure%20retail%20months.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20Neeter%20knew%20would%20increase%20revenue%20was%20the%20ability%20to%20have%20more%20people%20on%20court%20as%20a%20pickleball%20facility%20than%20a%20tennis%20facility.%20Four%20pickleball%20courts%20can%20easily%20fit%20on%20his%20one%20tennis%20court%2C%20which%20means%20he%20can%20have%20a%20lot%20more%20paying%20customers%20on%20court%20at%20the%20same%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20running%20a%20tennis-pickleball%20hybrid%20shop%20for%20a%20while%2C%20Neeter%20officially%20rebranded%20to%20the%20Santa%20Monica%20Pickleball%20Center%20in%20August%202023.%20He's%20still%20able%20to%20provide%20tennis%20lessons%20and%20clinics%20offsite%3B%20he%20got%20a%20license%20from%20the%20city%20that%20lets%20him%20rent%20courts%20by%20the%20hour%20at%20public%20parks%2C%20%26quot%3Bso%20we're%20still%20doing%20tennis%20on%20the%20outside%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20revenue%20numbers%20have%20never%20looked%20better.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221284%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22smpb%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6529bf9355f52b01b35fb322%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221034%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENeeter's%20goal%20is%20to%20%26quot%3Bbuild%20the%20best%20pickleball%20shop%20in%20the%20country%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20His%202%2C000-square-foot%20pro%20shop%20offers%20shoes%2C%20gear%2C%20and%2C%20of%20course%2C%20hundreds%20of%20paddles.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Jon%20Neeter%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt%20this%20point%20of%20this%20year%2C%20we're%20two%20times%20the%20revenue%20of%20our%20best%20year%20ever%20%E2%80%94%20and%20there's%20still%20the%20holiday%20season%20to%20go%20with%20retail%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Neeter.%20Insider%20viewed%20his%20profit%20and%20loss%20statements%20from%20the%20past%20five%20years%20to%20verify%20his%20tremendous%20revenue%20growth.%20In%202023%2C%20he's%20already%20done%20well%20over%20%241%20million%20in%20sales%20between%20retail%20and%20on-court%20services%20like%20lessons%20and%20clinics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20wouldn't%20be%20where%20he%20is%20today%20without%20taking%20a%20chance%20on%20pickleball%2C%20%26quot%3Bbut%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20I%20didn't%20think%20it%20was%20that%20much%20of%20a%20risk%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%20%26quot%3BBecause%20I%20just%20kind%20of%20resolved%20myself%20to%3A%20It's%20going%20to%20work.%20We're%20going%20to%20make%20it%20work%20because%20it%20has%20to%20work.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpickleball-business-owner-pivoted-from-tennis-revenue-sales-spiked-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697276521000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6529b24c68f1d46f52b1c1c2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpickleball-business-owner-pivoted-from-tennis-revenue-sales-spiked-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%26quot%3BRetail%20has%20done%20things%20I%20never%20thought%20it%20would.%20I%20knew%20it%20would%20be%20good%20but%20we're%20talking%20about%20having%20six-figure%20retail%20months%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20SMPB%20owner%20Jon%20Neeter.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kelkins%40businessinsider.com%20(Kathleen%20Elkins)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A8%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpickleball-business-owne