20part%20two%2C%20where%20all%20the%20evidence%20comes%20out%20about%20how%20he%20stole%20millions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228256%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Lawyer%20Willie%20Gary%20poses%20for%20a%20selfie%20with%20a%20guest%20at%20a%20screening%20for%20'The%20Burial.%26quot%3B%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6529a6e36561dd877e7aa48e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225504%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELawyer%20Willie%20Gary%20poses%20for%20a%20selfie%20with%20a%20guest%20at%20a%20screening%20of%20%26quot%3BThe%20Burial.%26quot%3B%20%3Cp%3EGrant%20Halverson%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3EWillie%20Gary's%20rags-to-riches%20story%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGary's%20rise%20from%20poverty%20to%20wealth%20is%20tailor-made%20for%20Hollywood.%20His%20father%20was%20a%20poor%20farmhand%20and%20Willie%2C%20born%20in%201947%2C%20%26quot%3Bspent%20much%20of%20his%20early%20childhood%20in%20a%20whitewashed%20three-room%20shack%20with%20a%20tar-paper%20roof%20and%20no%20electricity%20or%20plumbing%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20a%201999%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newyorker.com%2Fmagazine%2F1999%2F11%2F01%2Fthe-burial%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ENew%20Yorker%20story%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20was%20the%20inspiration%20for%20the%20new%20film.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20he%20spent%20much%20of%20his%20childhood%20working%20on%20vegetable%20farms%2C%20Gary%20made%20it%20through%20high%20school%2C%20went%20to%20college%20on%20a%20football%20scholarship%2C%20and%20then%20survived%20law%20school.%20He%20got%20a%20job%20in%20a%20Florida%20public%20defender's%20office%20for%20%2425%20a%20week%2C%20passed%20the%20bar%20exam%2C%20and%20started%20his%20own%20law%20firm%20in%201975%20after%20the%20public%20defender%20couldn't%20afford%20to%20keep%20him%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20didn't%20take%20long%20for%20him%20to%20develop%20an%20expertise%20in%20personal-injury%20cases.%20A%20%24225%2C000%20verdict%20here%2C%20a%20million-dollar%20judgment%20there%2C%20plus%20a%20%2440%20million%20settlement%20over%20a%20downed%20power%20line%20that%20electrocuted%20an%20entire%20family%20%E2%80%94%20by%20the%201990s%2C%20Gary%20and%20his%20growing%20firm%20were%20handling%20these%20cases%20at%20a%20steady%20clip.%20That's%20when%20the%20case%20that%20shot%20him%20to%20national%20stardom%20came%20calling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Burial%26quot%3B%20tells%20the%20story%20of%20Gary's%20work%20for%20Jeremiah%20O'Keefe%2C%20a%20Mississippi%20undertaker%20who%20sued%20a%20funeral-home%20conglomerate%20called%20the%20Loewen%20Group%20for%20reneging%20on%20a%20business%20deal.%20Gary%20transformed%20a%20dry%20contract%20dispute%20into%20a%20morality%20play%20that%20cast%20O'Keefe%20as%20an%20anti-Klan%20war%20hero%20and%20Loewen's%20CEO%20as%20a%20wheeler-dealer%20who%20jacked%20up%20casket%20prices%20on%20poor%20Mississippians%20and%20owned%20a%20giant%20yacht.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20filmmakers%20take%20a%20degree%20of%20artistic%20license%2C%20but%20some%20of%20the%20zaniest%20elements%2C%20like%20Gary's%20use%20of%20a%20private%20jet%20called%20%26quot%3BWings%20of%20Justice%2C%26quot%3B%20are%20true%20to%20life.%20So%20was%20the%20%24500%20million%20verdict%20that%20Gary%20won%20for%20O'Keefe.%20It%20was%20so%20large%2C%20Loewen%20couldn't%20even%20afford%20to%20appeal%20it%2C%20paying%20around%20%24175%20million%20to%20settle%20the%20case.%20Loewen%20even%20tried%20to%20sue%20the%20US%20government%2C%20claiming%20Gary%20had%20whipped%20up%20jurors%20with%20eagle-humping%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.buzzfeednews.com%2Farticle%2Fchrishamby%2Fhomegrown-disaster%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eanti-Canadian%20rhetoric%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20(The%20effort%20failed.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGary%20seems%20to%20like%20the%20movie%20and%20Foxx's%20portrayal.%20A%20private%20screening%20was%20arranged%20for%20Gary%20and%20his%20friends%20and%20family%2C%20and%20the%20Gary%20Parenti%20Facebook%20and%20Instagram%20pages%20are%20packed%20with%20clips.%20And%20the%20real%20Willie%20Gary%20makes%20a%20cameo%20in%20a%20post-credits%20stinger%2C%20running%20into%20Foxx's%20Gary%20in%20a%20courthouse%20hallway%20and%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20want%20to%20be%20just%20like%20you%20when%20I%20grow%20up!%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223504%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Attorney%20Willie%20Gary%20and%20Don%20King%20speak%20to%20the%20press%20in%202005.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6529a74868f1d46f52b1b326%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222336%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAttorney%20Willie%20Gary%20and%20his%20client%20Don%20King%20speaking%20to%20the%20press%20in%202005.%3Cp%3EJim%20McIsaac%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3EAccusations%20of%20sex%20misconduct%2C%20theft%2C%20and%20conflicts%20of%20interest%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20for%20every%20headline-grabbing%20case%20against%20a%20defendant%20like%20Loewen%2C%20Disney%2C%20or%20Anheuser-Busch%2C%20Gary's%20firm%20has%20handled%20scores%20of%20smaller%20ones.%20And%20it's%20in%20some%20of%20those%20cases%20where%20clients%20have%20turned%20on%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202003%2C%20dozens%20of%20women%20who%20sued%20Ford%20and%20a%20contractor%20over%20sexist%20managers%20turned%20around%20and%20sued%20Gary%2C%20their%20own%20lawyer%2C%20alleging%20that%20he%20secretly%20schemed%20to%20pay%20himself%20more%20money%20than%20he%20got%20for%20his%20clients.%20Of%20the%20%2416%20million%20paid%20to%20settle%20the%20case%2C%20Gary%20and%20his%20firm%20helped%20themselves%20to%20over%20%249%20million%2C%20according%20to%20court%20documents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20court%20records%2C%20Gary%20argued%20that%20he'd%20secured%20untold%20millions%20in%20%26quot%3Bprogrammatic%20relief%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20corporate%20policy%20changes.%20But%20unlike%20in%20a%20class%20action%2C%20where%20settlements%20are%20public%2C%20the%20Ford%20deal%20was%20hush-hush%20%E2%80%94%20so%20much%20so%2C%20one%20of%20the%20women%20alleges%20in%20the%20lawsuit%2C%20that%20one%20of%20Gary's%20cocounsels%20told%20her%20that%20she'd%20end%20up%20%26quot%3Bin%20a%20body%20bag%26quot%3B%20if%20she%20didn't%20return%20a%20spreadsheet%20she%20was%20accidentally%20given%20that%20revealed%20the%20details.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELawrence%20Fox%2C%20an%20ethics%20expert%20the%20women%20hired%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdrive.google.com%2Ffile%2Fd%2F1DfLQYa_k6KXp5uUsI7xPQ-FYCQ_TpTCP%2Fview%3Fusp%3Dsharing%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Esaid%20in%20a%20report%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20court%20that%20the%20Gary%20firm%20did%20essentially%20no%20work%20for%20%246%20million%20of%20the%20%249%20million%20it%20received.%20The%20firm%20was%20%26quot%3Bliterally%20taking%20money%20out%20of%20the%20hands%20of%20their%20clients%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%20He%20called%20the%20Gary%20firm's%20behavior%20%26quot%3Bunethical%2C%20even%20criminal.%26quot%3B%20What's%20worse%2C%20Fox%20wrote%2C%20is%20that%20Gary%20%26quot%3Bapplied%20the%20very%20same%20modus%20operandi%26quot%3B%20when%20it%20sued%20other%20companies%2C%20which%20the%20report%20did%20not%20name.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20New%20Yorker%2C%20Gary%20also%20made%20an%20agreement%20with%20the%20Loewen%20Group%20that%20one%20ethics%20expert%20questioned.%20As%20part%20of%20its%20nine-figure%20settlement%2C%20the%20company%20paid%20Gary%20a%20%2420%2C000-a-year%20retainer%20for%20three%20years%20upon%20settling%20the%20O'Keefe%20case%20so%20he%20couldn't%20sue%20them%20again%2C%20the%20New%20Yorker%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESuch%20deals%20are%20banned%20under%20many%20states'%20ethics%20rules%2C%20according%20to%20Bruce%20Green%2C%20a%20law%20professor%20at%20Fordham.%20If%20businesses%20can%20pay%20to%20keep%20attorneys%20who%20win%20against%20them%20out%20of%20play%2C%20prospective%20clients%20can't%20hire%20a%20lawyer%20who%20knows%20the%20defendant's%20weak%20spots.%20Gary%20taking%20on%20Loewen%20as%20a%20client%2C%20Green%20said%20in%20an%20email%2C%20looks%20like%20a%20%26quot%3Bpretext%26quot%3B%20to%20get%20around%20the%20ban.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Ford%20case%20settled%20on%20confidential%20terms.%20At%20around%20the%20same%20time%2C%20some%20Black%20employees%20of%20Coca-Cola%20began%20to%20complain%20that%20Gary%20didn't%20deliver%20on%20his%20promises%20to%20get%20more%20money%20for%20them%20than%20they%20could've%20received%20through%20a%20%24192%20million%20class-action%20settlement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20Coke%20employees%2C%20Sharron%20Mangum%2C%20said%20Gary%20sexually%20assaulted%20her%20in%20April%202002%2C%20when%20both%20of%20them%20were%20in%20New%20York%20City%20for%20the%20Coca-Cola%20shareholders'%20meeting.%20She%20said%20he%20made%20overtures%20for%20months%2C%20suggesting%20that%20she%20visit%20him%20in%20Florida%20and%20go%20on%20%26quot%3Bintimate%20excursions.%26quot%3B%20In%20a%20stretch%20limo%20in%20New%20York%2C%20she%20said%2C%20he%20began%20to%20touch%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMr.%20Gary%20proceeded%20to%20roll%20up%20the%20dark%2C%20divider%20glass%20window%20inside%20the%20limousine%2C%20restricting%20any%20visual%20and%20audio%20contact%20of%20the%20driver%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20wrote%20in%20a%202017%20letter%20to%20the%20FBI.%20%26quot%3BMr.%20Gary%20then%20attacked%20me%20%E2%80%94%20grabbing%20my%20breast%2C%20grabbing%20between%20my%20legs%2C%20forcibly%20placing%20my%20hand%20on%20his%20penis%20and%20trying%20to%20force%20his%20tongue%20into%20my%20mouth.%26quot%3B%20In%20the%20letter%2C%20she%20said%20Gary%20only%20stopped%20when%20she%20threatened%20to%20jump%20out%20of%20the%20car.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20Mangum's%20close%20friends%2C%20who%20asked%20not%20to%20be%20named%2C%20told%20Insider%20she%20recalled%20Mangum%20calling%20her%20about%20the%20episode%20shortly%20after%20it%20happened.%20And%20Marietta%20Goodman%2C%20another%20former%20client%20of%20Gary's%20in%20the%20Coke%20actions%2C%20said%20she%20remembered%20Mangum%20telling%20her%20about%20it%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInsider%20viewed%20copies%20of%20complaints%20Mangum%20said%20she%20filed%20against%20Gary%20with%20the%20Florida%20Bar%20Association%20in%202003%20and%20again%20in%202021%20which%20mentioned%20her%20claims%20of%20Gary's%20sexual%20misconduct%2C%20and%20the%20letter%20she%20wrote%20to%20the%20FBI.%20Neither%20complaint%20resulted%20in%20discipline%2C%20and%20Gary%20was%20never%20criminally%20charged.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202007%2C%20one%20of%20Gary's%20secretaries%2C%20Jillian%20Nedd%2C%20accused%20him%20of%20rape.%20After%20police%20dropped%20a%20criminal%20investigation%2C%20Gary%20sued%20her%20for%20extortion.%20(According%20to%20the%20Palm%20Beach%20Post%2C%20the%20suit%20ended%20in%202008%20with%20Nedd%20and%20two%20co-defendants%20paying%20Gary%20%24100%20each.)%20In%20turn%2C%20Nedd%20sued%20Gary%2C%20claiming%20%26quot%3Bsexual%20battery%20and%20rape.%26quot%3B%20Nedd's%20lawsuit%20settled%20in%202010.%20Neither%20side%20revealed%20the%20terms%20of%20that%20settlement%2C%20though%20Palm%20Beach%20Post%20reported%20that%20other%20women%20had%20been%20interviewed%20as%20part%20of%20the%20discovery%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20recently%2C%20a%20Georgia%20woman%20named%20Ardria%20Clark%20sued%20Gary%2C%20claiming%20that%20he%20took%20money%20from%20a%20car-crash%20settlement%20he'd%20won%20for%20Clark's%20mother%20and%20secretly%20paid%20it%20to%20Clark's%20sister%2C%20Tamesha%20Marshall-Pharr%2C%20who%20Clark%20claims%20was%20having%20sex%20with%20one%20of%20Gary's%20sons%20and%20possibly%20with%20Gary%20himself.%20Marshall-Pharr%20was%20murdered%20by%20her%20husband%20after%20he%20found%20out%2C%20Clark%20claimed.%20The%20case%20is%20pending.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Willie%20Gary%20watching%20Jamie%20Foxx%20play%20himself%20in%20%26quot%3BThe%20Burial.%26quot%3B%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6529a7bd68f1d46f52b1b3cf%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWillie%20Gary%20watching%20Jamie%20Foxx%20play%20himself%20in%20%26quot%3BThe%20Burial.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EGrant%20Halverson%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3E'Giant%20killer'%20or%20'client%20killer%3F'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERay%20Rogers%2C%20a%20consultant%20for%20activists%20and%20unions%2C%20has%20become%20a%20persistent%20thorn%20in%20Gary's%20side.%20He%20hosts%20years%20worth%20of%20legal%20filings%20and%20testimonies%20on%20a%20site%20he%20runs%20called%20TheClientKiller.org%2C%20a%20play%20on%20Gary's%20%26quot%3Bgiant%20killer%26quot%3B%20moniker%2C%20and%20since%202021%2C%20he%20has%20run%20a%20website%20urging%20Amazon%20to%20%26quot%3BBury%20'The%20Burial.'%26quot%3B%20He's%20tried%20to%20buy%20a%20billboard%20bashing%20Gary%20in%20his%20hometown%20and%20leafleted%20at%20his%20public%20appearances%20to%20try%20to%20stop%20people%20from%20hiring%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20kept%20him%20out%20of%20the%20Flint%2C%20Michigan%2C%20water%20crisis%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Rogers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20Gary's%20upset%20clients%20filed%20complaints%20with%20the%20Florida%20bar%2C%20but%20none%20of%20them%20appear%20to%20have%20gone%20anywhere.%20(He%20was%20lightly%20disciplined%20by%20the%20state%20bar%20twice%2C%20once%20in%201993%20and%20once%20in%201994.)%20Willie%20Lewis%2C%20whose%20stepfather%20Troy%20Fulks%20Jr.%20hired%20Gary%20to%20go%20after%20Florida%20Power%20%26amp%3B%20Light%20after%20most%20of%20his%20family%20was%20electrocuted%20by%20a%20downed%20line%2C%20said%20Fulks%20was%20supposed%20to%20get%20the%20lion's%20share%20of%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sun-sentinel.com%2F1985%2F04%2F25%2Ffpl-pays-millions-to-kin-of-electrocuted-family%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ereported%20%2440%20million%20settlement%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELewis%20said%20Fulks%20was%20a%20barely%20literate%20farm%20worker%20who%20didn't%20have%20anybody%20looking%20out%20for%20him%2C%20and%20he%20still%20hangs%20on%20to%20decades-old%20records%20of%20disbursements%20and%20court%20records%20in%20hopes%20of%20getting%20answers.%20He%20and%20Rogers%20say%20they've%20only%20found%20records%20of%20about%20%243%20million%20in%20disbursements%20and%20say%20Gary%20never%20accounted%20for%20where%20the%20money%20went.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20response%20to%20a%20bar%20complaint%2C%20Gary%20said%20he%20had%20long%20since%20thrown%20out%20Fulks'%20file%2C%20but%20said%20it's%20possible%20that%20Fulks%20sold%20his%20structured%20settlement%20payments%20to%20a%20third%20party%20for%20dimes%20on%20the%20dollar.%20Lewis%20rejected%20that%20claim.%20%26quot%3BYou%20can't%20sell%20what%20you%20don't%20have%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20in%20a%20text%20message.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEsposito%2C%20the%20woman%20who%20hired%20Gary%20to%20go%20after%20another%20lawyer%20who%20allegedly%20groped%20her%20and%20solicited%20sex%20from%20her%2C%20said%20Gary%20%26quot%3Bjust%20walked%20off%20into%20the%20sunset%26quot%3B%20after%20they%20lost%20a%20key%20motion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20she%20received%20evidence%20from%20a%20lender%20that%20Gary%20had%20paid%20back%20money%20she'd%20borrowed%20against%20her%20case%2C%20Esposito%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdrive.google.com%2Ffile%2Fd%2F1tXWvnCkaDaSPHu6-3tE1bZZ0RmwI5Wmj%2Fview%3Fusp%3Dsharing%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Easserted%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20court%20filing%20that%20he%20secretly%20settled%20her%20case%20and%20kept%20the%20money.%20Gary%20told%20Florida%20bar%20officials%20that%20he%20had%20done%20no%20such%20thing%2C%20and%20said%20Esposito's%20case%20had%20major%20weaknesses%20that%20he%20tried%20to%20help%20her%20overcome.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lawsuits%20are%20ongoing.%20Elliott%2C%20whose%20daughter%20was%20killed%20in%20a%20Georgia%20car%20wreck%2C%20accused%20Gary%20and%20his%20firm%20of%20malpractice.%20She%20settled%20her%20case%20against%20him%20last%20fall%20%E2%80%94%20and%20Gary's%20firm%20promptly%20missed%20a%20payment%2C%20leading%20the%20%24579%2C000%20settlement%20to%20become%20public.%20She%20has%20so%20far%20managed%20to%20seize%20%24102%2C000%20from%20an%20account%20the%20Gary%20firm%20had%20with%20Truist.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EElliott%20called%20Gary%20a%20%26quot%3Bmonster%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bscum%20of%20the%20earth%26quot%3B%20and%20said%20she%20was%20upset%20that%20he's%20the%20subject%20of%20a%20movie.%20She%20said%20he%20showed%20up%20to%20a%20mediation%20last%20year%20with%20a%20cane%20and%20that%20his%20lawyer%20claimed%20he%20was%20suffering%20from%20memory%20problems.%20Gary%2C%20she%20said%2C%20never%20apologized%20%E2%80%94%20and%20when%20they%20passed%20in%20the%20hall%2C%20he%20didn't%20even%20meet%20her%20gaze.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20person%20that%20he%20claims%20to%20be%20in%20this%20movie%20is%20totally%20a%20lie%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BFor%20a%20person%20that%20can't%20remember%2C%20can't%20hardly%20walk%2C%20but%20you're%20making%20movies%2C%20you're%20flying%20in%20and%20out%20of%20the%20country%20--%20how%20are%20you%20doing%20this%20with%20no%20money%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20other%20signs%20that%20Gary%20might%20not%20be%20quite%20what%20he%20used%20to%20be.%20He%20and%20his%20firm%20had%20legal%20scuffles%20with%20the%20IRS%20and%20creditors%20in%202012.%20As%20recently%20as%20this%20August%2C%20the%20lender%20Law%20Finance%20Group%20registered%20a%20%245%20million%20judgment%20against%20Gary%20and%20his%20firm%20in%20Florida%20state%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20old%20%26quot%3BWings%20of%20Justice%26quot%3B%20jet%20has%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fabpic.co.uk%2Fpictures%2Fview%2F1360648%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Escrapped%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20the%20federal%20registration%20on%20%26quot%3BWings%20of%20Justice%20II%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20luxuriously%20appointed%20Boeing%20737%2C%20lapsed%20in%202018%3B%20the%20last%20photograph%20that%20Insider%20could%20find%20of%20the%20jet%20showed%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jetphotos.com%2Fphoto%2F9641084%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eapparently%20mothballed%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20a%20Florida%20airport%20in%202017.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprojects.propublica.org%2Fnonprofits%2Forganizations%2F650873650%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EThe%20Gary%20Foundation%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20family%20foundation%2C%20hasn't%20reported%20more%20than%20%2450%2C000%20in%20annual%20revenue%20to%20the%20IRS%20since%20at%20least%202011%2C%20when%20it%20had%20just%20%2410%2C000%20on%20hand.%20But%20a%20piece%20authored%20by%20Gary's%20PR%20person%20Debra%20Sweeting%20earlier%20this%20year%20refers%20to%20the%20foundation%20as%20though%20it's%20still%20active%2C%20and%20says%20he%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewestsidegazette.com%2Fthe-burial-with-jamie-foxx-starring-as-willie-gary-debuts-next-month%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eoften%20travels%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20on%20the%20jet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGary%20didn't%20respond%20to%20emails%20for%20this%20story.%20Asked%20about%20the%20allegations%20on%20Rogers'%20websites%2C%20Sweeting%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bwe're%20not%20interested%20in%20commenting%20on%20bogus%20websites.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmazon%20quietly%20released%20%26quot%3BThe%20Burial%26quot%3B%20in%20theaters%20for%20one%20week%20before%20it%20debuts%20on%20streaming%2C%20a%20move%20a%20studio%20often%20makes%20when%20they%20believe%20that%20they%20have%20a%20potential%20award-winning%20film%20on%20its%20hands.%20Variety%20has%20called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Ffeature%2F2024-oscars-best-pic