3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3Euncannily%20familiar%3B%20I%20had%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ecome%20across%20it%20ever%20so%20often%20in%20books%20and%20in%20museums.%20The%20tree%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eand%20its%20radiating%20branches%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ereminded%20me%20of%20the%20iconic%C2%A0figurines%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eof%20earth%20goddesses%20from%20the%20time%20of%20the%20Indus%20valley%20civilisation%20or%20earlier.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEvoking%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ethe%20form%20of%20an%20earth%20goddess%20in%20the%20contours%20of%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ethis%20stately%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Etree%20was%20an%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eepiphanic%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Emoment.%20It%20enabled%20me%20to%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eintuit%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20in%20an%20almost%20tactile%20manner%2C%20the%20creative%20gaze%20that%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Emust%20have%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eshaped%20the%20iconography%20of%20the%20earth%20goddess%2C%20its%20conceptual%20clarity.%20Her%20body%2C%20sprouting%20vine%20and%20leaf%2C%20was%20human%20and%20vegetal%20in%20form%2C%20as%20if%20part%20of%20a%20continuum%20%E2%80%93%20a%20profound%20visualisation%20of%20an%20entwined%20existence.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20179px)%2085vw%2C%20179px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F12101730%2Fpic-3-earth-goddess.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22179%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F12101730%2Fpic-3-earth-goddess.jpg%20542w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F12101730%2Fpic-3-earth-goddess-141x300.jpg%20141w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F12101730%2Fpic-3-earth-goddess-482x1024.jpg%20482w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-679614%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22380%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20same%20semal%20tree%20from%20a%20different%20angle.%20Photo%3A%20Chitra%20Padmanabhan%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20visibly%20powerful%20figure%20of%20the%20earth%20goddess%2C%20symbolic%20of%20the%20female%20fertility%20principle%2C%20was%20an%20expression%20of%20fecundity%20%E2%80%94%20the%20secret%20knowledge%20of%20life%20and%20abundance%20that%20was%20necessary%20for%20survival.%20In%20this%20case%2C%20fecundity%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ein%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eboth%20nature%20and%20humans.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20fact%20that%20the%20figurines%20were%20moulded%20from%20fertile%20clay%2C%20evoking%20the%20magic%20of%20earth%20and%20grain%20so%20central%20to%20the%20vitality%20of%20a%20river%20valley%20civilisation%2C%20completed%20the%20circle%20of%20creativity%20seeded%20by%20nature.%20Within%20this%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ecycle%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eof%20creativity%20lay%20the%20organic%20beginnings%20of%20art%20and%20mythology%2C%20a%20culture%20grounded%20in%20material%20existence.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESaying%20a%20silent%20thank%20you%20to%20the%20semal%20tree%2C%20which%20had%20transformed%20a%20familiar%20path%20into%20an%20unfamiliar%20world%20waiting%20to%20be%20discovered%2C%20I%20decided%20to%20spend%20some%20time%20looking%20at%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ethe%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Etrees%20in%20the%20squirrel-free%20zone.%20I%20was%20sure%C2%A0my%20green%20friends%20would%20prompt%20more%20instances%20of%20time%20travel.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EClose%20by%2C%C2%A0I%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0spotted%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ea%20karanja%20tree%20with%20a%20well-rounded%20trunk%2C%20lush%20with%20leaves%2C%20curving%20above%20the%20walking%20path%20like%C2%A0a%20gateway.%20Something%20about%20the%20curve%20of%20the%20trunk%20jogged%20my%20memory.%20Then%20I%20remembered.%20Almost%20two%20decades%20ago%2C%20I%20had%20visited%20Sanchi%2C%C2%A0drawn%20by%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ethe%20powerful%20pull%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%93%20in%20all%20its%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Esimplicity%20%E2%80%93%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eof%20the%20Buddhist%20stupa.%20Later%2C%20wandering%20around%20I%20came%20face-to-face%20with%20the%20much-talked%20about%20detail%20on%20the%20eastern%20gateway%20%E2%80%93%20the%20motif%20of%20a%20tree%20spirit%20grasping%20a%20branch%20so%20that%20it%20formed%20a%20curved%20arch%20above%20her%2C%20just%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Elike%20the%20curve%20of%20the%C2%A0karanja%20tree%20trunk%20before%20me.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F12101924%2FUntitled-design-1-2.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F12101924%2FUntitled-design-1-2.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F12101924%2FUntitled-design-1-2-300x169.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F12101924%2FUntitled-design-1-2-1024x576.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-679615%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22675%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3E(Left%20to%20right)%20The%20bent%20bough%20of%20a%20karanja%20tree%20in%20the%20author%E2%80%99s%20neighbourhood%20evokes%20the%20memory%20of%20the%20famous%20salabhanjika%20motif%20on%20the%20eastern%20gateway%20of%20the%20Sanchi%20stupa.%20Photos%3A%20Chitra%20Padmanabhan%2C%20Wikimedia%20commons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShe%20was%20a%20salabhanjika%2C%20spirit%20of%20the%20sal%20tree%2C%20under%20which%20the%20Buddha%20was%20born%2C%20and%20was%20therefore%20celebrated%20as%20a%20symbol%20of%20fertility%20and%20auspiciousness.%C2%A0%C2%A0In%20the%20motif%20of%20the%20salabhanjika%2C%20depicted%20as%20a%C2%A0full-breasted%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ewoman%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eholding%20a%20branch%20bent%20under%20the%20weight%20of%20abundant%20fruit%2C%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ethe%20connect%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ethe%20creative%20eye%20makes%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ebetween%20humans%20and%20nature%C2%A0was%20clearly%20evident.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENow%20my%20imagination%20was%20in%20full%20flow%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3ENear%20the%20spot%20where%20I%20usually%20conclude%20my%20walk%2C%20I%C2%A0came%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20upon%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Emy%20third%20valuable%20%E2%80%98excavation%E2%80%99%20of%20the%20day%2C%20one%20that%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Epulled%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eme%20back%20from%204000%20years%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20right%20in%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eto%20the%2020%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eth%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20century.%20This%20semal%20tree%20could%20easily%20have%20been%20a%20Ramkinkar%20Baij%20figure%20of%20a%20strong%20and%20graceful%20Santhal%20woman%20or%20a%20sister%20sculpture%20of%20Baij%E2%80%99s%20Sujata%2C%20standing%20outdoors%20in%20the%20midst%20of%20a%20grove%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ein%20Santiniketan%2C%20herself%20like%20a%20willowy%20tree.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F12104616%2FScreenshot-2023-10-12-at-10.45.0.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221052%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F12104616%2FScreenshot-2023-10-12-at-10.45.0.png%201052w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F12104616%2FScreenshot-2023-10-12-at-10.45.0-300x296.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F12104616%2FScreenshot-2023-10-12-at-10.45.0-1024x1010.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-679631%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221038%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EOne%20can%20be%20forgiven%20for%20thinking%20that%20the%20semal%20tree%20(right)%20is%20also%20a%20sculpture%20meant%20to%20be%20placed%20close%20to%20Ramkinkar%20Baij%E2%80%99s%20outdoor%20sculpture%20Sujata%20in%20Santiniketan%20(left).%20Photos%3A%20https%3A%2F%2Fcommons.wikimedia.org%2Fwiki%2FFile%3ASujata_-_1935_CE_-_Ramkinkar_Baij_-_Santiniketan_2014-06-29_5354.JPG%2C%20Chitra%20Padmanabhan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20had%20experienced%20the%20tug%20of%20a%20creative%20instinct%20birthed%20by%20the%20elemental%20relationship%20between%20nature%20and%20humans%20on%20an%20earlier%20occasion%2C%20more%20than%20a%20decade%20ago.%20In%2012%20hours%2C%20courtesy%20a%20train%20and%20cab%20journey%2C%20I%20had%20travelled%20back%20in%20time%20to%20about%2010%2C000%20years%20ago%3A%20from%20Delhi%20to%20Bhopal%20and%2040%20odd%20kms%20onward%20to%20a%20world%20heritage%20site%20with%20a%20name%20like%20an%20incantation%20%E2%80%93%20Bhimbetka.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20people%20irresistibly%20attracted%20to%20%E2%80%98beginnings%E2%80%99%2C%20it%20can%E2%80%99t%20get%20more%20dramatic%20than%20Bhimbetka%E2%80%99s%20massive%20sandstone%20rocks%20emerging%20from%20the%20warm%20clasp%20of%20the%20central%20Indian%20forest%20in%20the%20Vindhyan%20range.%20A%20terrain%20blessed%20with%20vegetation%2C%20water%20and%20animal%20life.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20was%20on%20these%20natural%20rock%20shelter%20surfaces%20that%20our%20ancestors%20inscribed%20themselves%20into%20the%20evolutionary%20timeline%20by%20painting%20their%20hunting%20and%20gathering%20lives%20with%20immediacy%20and%20spell-binding%20directness.%C2%A0%C2%A0They%20painted%20a%20landscape%20abounding%20with%20wild%20boar%2C%20neelgai%2C%20monkeys%2C%20elephants%2C%20peacocks%2C%20and%20tigers%3B%20bison%C2%A0and%20bulls%20caught%20in%20motion%3B%20hunting%20scenes%20and%20the%20heat%20of%20battle%3B%20communal%20dance%20and%20convivial%20moments.%20These%20images%20heralded%20the%20early%20cultures%20of%20hunting%20and%20food%20gathering%20humans.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20journey%20to%20Bhimbetka%20was%20like%20reading%20a%20script%20backwards.%20From%20the%20vantage%20point%20of%20the%2021%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Est%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0century%2C%20one%20was%20bound%20for%20a%20site%20that%20was%20pre-historic%20and%20non-denominational%2C%20bearing%20the%20imprint%20of%20humankind%E2%80%99s%20beginnings.%20A%20time%20before%20script%2C%20before%20religion%2C%20but%20with%20the%20powerful%2C%20invocatory%20art%20of%20drawing%20that%20had%20the%20power%20to%20bring%20a%20world%20into%20being.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDuring%20the%20final%20stretch%20of%20our%20cab%20ride%20%E2%80%93%20I%20was%20travelling%20with%20my%20shutterbug%20niece%2C%20Kavita%20%E2%80%93%20we%20had%20our%20first%20glimpse%20of%20the%20sandstone%20rocks.%20From%20a%20distance%2C%20in%20silhouette%2C%20they%20looked%20like%20a%20procession%20of%20Jurassic%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ebehemoths.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20moment%20we%20set%20foot%20on%20the%20lush%20pathway%20leading%20to%20the%20rock%20shelters%2C%20we%20were%20enveloped%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ein%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ea%20sense%20of%20timelessness.%20A%20deep%20silence%20hung%20over%20the%20place.%20In%20the%20crisp%20sunlight%20each%20verdant%20leaf%20stood%20out%20sharply%20as%20if%20backlit.%20Strangely%2C%20we%20felt%20our%20vision%20becoming%20sharper%2C%20too.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20gigantic%20rocks%20seemed%20like%20works%20of%20art%20themselves%2C%20having%20been%20sculpted%20in%20time%20by%20sweeping%20winds.%20Some%20looked%20like%20natural%20fortifications%2C%20others%20like%20denizens%20of%20the%20animal%20world%20%E2%80%93%20giant%20turtle%2C%20lion%2C%20frog%20poised%20for%20a%20leap%2C%20and%20a%20beak-nosed%20bird.%20It%20was%20not%20difficult%20to%20imagine%20stories%20of%20the%20origin%20of%20the%20universe%20being%20inspired%20by%20them.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESeeing%20the%20patterns%20created%20by%20perforations%20in%20leaves%2C%20peeling%20bark%2C%20and%20weathering%20marks%20on%20sandstone%20surfaces%2C%20it%20was%20easy%20to%20imagine%20our%20ancestors%20wanting%20to%20paint%20their%20faces%20and%20bodies%20similarly%2C%20their%C2%A0search%20for%20colours%20leading%20them%2C%20but%20naturally%2C%20to%20the%20plants%20and%20rocks.%20The%20purpose%3A%20to%20be%20one%20with%20the%20environment%2C%20for%20camouflage%2C%20as%20clan%20identity%C2%A0or%20for%20ritualistic%20purposes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F12102811%2Fpic_8-1.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F12102811%2Fpic_8-1.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%