016%20years%2C%20and%20already%20gone%20through%20five%20major%20brutal%20wars%2C%20which%20remain%20unaccounted%20for%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThey%20also%20expressed%20concern%20about%20reports%20that%20journalists%20and%20media%20workers%20reporting%20on%20the%20conflict%20had%20been%20targeted%2C%20with%20seven%20Palestinian%20journalists%20and%20media%20workers%20reportedly%20killed%20in%20Israeli%20airstrikes.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETheir%20statement%20asserted%20that%20%E2%80%9Cindiscriminately%20killing%20civilians%20in%20the%20context%20of%20hostilities%2C%20with%20no%20regard%20for%20the%20principles%20of%20distinction%2C%20precaution%20and%20proportionality%2C%20is%20a%20war%20crime%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20experts%20had%20also%20expressed%20their%20shock%20at%20the%20language%20of%20the%20Israeli%20defence%20minister%20in%20cutting%20off%20essential%20supplies%20to%20Gaza%2C%20who%20had%20stated%20that%20the%20authorities%20are%20fighting%20%E2%80%9Chuman%20animals%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CBesides%20this%20appalling%20language%20that%20dehumanises%20the%20Palestinian%20people%2C%20especially%20those%20who%20have%20been%20unlawfully%20%E2%80%9Cimprisoned%E2%80%9D%20in%20Gaza%20for%2016%20years%2C%20we%20condemn%20the%20withholding%20of%20essential%20supplies%20such%20as%20food%2C%20water%2C%20electricity%20and%20medicines.%20Such%20actions%20will%20precipitate%20a%20severe%20humanitarian%20crisis%20in%20Gaza%2C%20where%20its%20population%20is%20now%20at%20inescapable%20risk%20of%20starvation.%20Intentional%20starvation%20is%20a%20crime%20against%20humanity%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20experts%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%20on%20Thursday%20had%20nuanced%20its%20initial%20response%20to%20the%20terror%20attack%20on%20Saturday%20by%20adding%20that%20Tel%20Aviv%20also%20had%20an%20obligation%20to%20follow%20international%20humanitarian%20law.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Six%20Takeaways%20from%20the%20Israel-Palestine%20Conflict%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fsix-takeaways-from-the-israel-palestine-conflict%5C%22%3ESix%20Takeaways%20from%20the%20Israel-Palestine%20Conflict%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EWhat%20is%20international%20humanitarian%20law%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20per%20the%20Red%20Cross%2C%20international%20humanitarian%20law%20(IHL)%20is%20a%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fblogs.icrc.org%2Filot%2F2017%2F08%2F07%2Ftreaties-make-international-humanitarian-law%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Edefined%20set%20of%20rules%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20seeks%2C%20for%20humanitarian%20reasons%2C%20to%20limit%C2%A0the%20effects%20of%20armed%20conflict%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0The%20concept%20of%20modern%20humanitarian%20law%20is%20more%20than%20150%20years%20old%2C%20with%20experts%20stating%20that%20it%20began%20with%20the%20Geneva%20Convention%20of%201864.%20The%20key%20treaties%20that%20form%20the%20foundation%20of%20IHL%20are%20the%201949%20Geneva%20Convention%20and%20its%20additional%20protocol%20signed%20in%201977.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20contrast%20to%20the%20UN%20charter%2C%20which%20talks%20about%20whether%20a%20state%20can%20resort%20to%20armed%20force%2C%20IHL%20regulates%20the%20conduct%20of%20parties%20in%20an%20armed%20conflict%20or%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ejus%20in%20bello%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EWhat%20international%20humanitarian%20law%20applies%20to%20the%20current%20conflict%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EProtection%20of%20civilians%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20key%20underlying%20theme%20of%20IHL%20is%20that%20civilians%20should%20not%20be%20targeted%20in%20any%20conflict%20and%20must%20be%20distinguished%20from%20fighters.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EUnder%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fihl-databases.icrc.org%2Fen%2Fihl-treaties%2Fapi-1977%2Farticle-57%3FactiveTab%3Dundefined%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Erules%20of%20waging%20war%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9Ceffective%20advance%20warning%20shall%20be%20given%20of%20attacks%20which%20may%20affect%20the%20civilian%20population%2C%20unless%20circumstances%20do%20not%20permit%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIsrael%20gave%20a%20notice%20of%2024%20hours%20to%20remove%20more%20than%20a%20million%20people%20from%20north%20Gaza.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHuman%20Rights%20Watch%20stated%20that%20the%20definition%20of%20%E2%80%9Ceffective%E2%80%9D%20depends%20on%20the%20circumstances.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CSuch%20an%20assessment%20would%20take%20into%20account%20the%20timing%20of%20the%20warning%20and%20the%20ability%20of%20civilians%20to%20leave%20the%20area.%20A%20warning%20that%20does%20not%20give%20civilians%20adequate%20time%20to%20leave%20for%20a%20safer%20area%20would%20not%20be%20considered%20%E2%80%9Ceffective%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hrw.org%2Fnews%2F2023%2F10%2F09%2Fquestions-and-answers-october-2023-hostilities-between-israel-and-palestinian-armed%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eit%20said%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFurther%2C%20the%20provision%20of%20the%20Additional%20Protocol%20makes%20it%20clear%20that%20even%20after%20an%20%E2%80%9Ceffective%20advance%20warning%E2%80%9D%2C%20civilians%20should%20not%20be%20targeted.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CNo%20provision%20of%20this%20Article%20may%20be%20construed%20as%20authorizing%20any%20attacks%20against%20the%20civilian%20population%2C%20civilians%20or%20civilian%20objects%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.icrc.org%2Fen%2Fdoc%2Fassets%2Ffiles%2Fother%2Ficrc_002_0321.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EAdditional%20Protocol%20I%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99s%20Article%2057%20on%20Precautions%20in%20Attack.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2F3ud__248-KY%3Fsi%3DenjncPnWumOaLBx4%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBesides%2C%20Article%2055%20(b)%20also%20notes%20that%20an%20attack%20is%20prohibited%20in%20law%20if%20it%20%E2%80%9Cmay%20be%20expected%20to%20cause%20incidental%20loss%20of%20civilian%20life%2C%20injury%20to%20civilians%2C%20damage%20to%20civilian%20objects%2C%20or%20a%20combination%20thereof%2C%20which%20would%20be%20excessive%20in%20relation%20to%20the%20concrete%20and%20direct%20military%20advantage%20anticipated%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ERight%20to%20self-defence%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20UN%20charter%20prohibits%20all%20kinds%20of%20armed%20conflict%2C%20except%20in%20%E2%80%9Cself-defence%E2%80%9D.%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20argument%20when%20it%20invaded%20Gaza%20in%20the%20past%20also%20relied%20upon%20the%20rules%20for%20going%20to%20war%20or%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ejus%20ad%20bellum%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.un.org%2Fen%2Fabout-us%2Fun-charter%2Fchapter-7%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EChapter%207%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20of%20the%20charter%20lists%20the%20%E2%80%9Cactions%20with%20respect%20to%20threats%20to%20the%20peace%2C%20breaches%20of%20the%20peace%2C%20and%20acts%20of%20aggression%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20per%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.culawreview.org%2Fjournal%2Fthe-self-defense-principle-re-examined-the-israel-palestine-conflict-in-international-law%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E2021%20paper%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20published%20in%20the%20Columbia%20Law%20School%20Undergraduate%20Review%2C%20there%20is%20no%20formal%20definition%20in%20international%20law%20doctrine%20for%20the%20term%20%E2%80%9Caggression%E2%80%9D%2C%20which%20gives%20states%20leeway%20in%20justifying%20war.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFurther%2C%20the%20paper%20said%20that%20%E2%80%9CIsrael%E2%80%99s%20repeated%20use%20of%20the%20self-defence%20argument%20also%20directly%20threatens%20the%20distinction%20between%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ejus%20ad%20bellum%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Eand%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ejus%20in%20bello%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ELaw%20of%20proportionality%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20rule%20of%20proportionality%20in%20relation%20to%20the%20protection%20of%20civilians%20and%20civilian%20property%20was%20codified%20first%20in%20Additional%20Protocol%E2%80%99s%20Article%2051%20(5)%20(b)%2C%20which%20states%20that%20an%20attack%20would%20be%20considered%20%E2%80%9Cindiscriminate%E2%80%9D%20if%20it%20may%20be%20%E2%80%9Cexpected%20to%20cause%20incidental%20loss%20of%20civilian%20life%2C%20injury%20to%20civilians%2C%20damage%20to%20civilian%20objects%2C%20or%20a%20combination%20thereof%2C%20which%20would%20be%20excessive%20in%20relation%20to%20the%20concrete%20and%20direct%20military%20advantage%20anticipated%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fimage.guardian.co.uk%2Fsys-files%2FGuardian%2Fdocuments%2F2009%2F09%2F15%2FUNFFMGCReport.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E2009%20report%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20of%20the%20United%20Nations%20fact-finding%20mission%20on%20the%20Gaza%20conflict%20found%20that%20%E2%80%9Cin%20the%20framing%20of%20Israeli%20military%20objectives%20with%20regard%20to%20the%20Gaza%20operations%2C%20the%20concept%20of%20Hamas%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%9Csupporting%20infrastructure%E2%80%9D%20is%20particularly%20worrying%20as%20it%20appears%20to%20transform%20civilians%20and%20civilian%20objects%20into%20legitimate%20targets%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CStatements%20by%20Israeli%20political%20and%20military%20leaders%20prior%20to%20and%20during%20the%20military%20operations%20in%20Gaza%20indicate%20that%20the%20Israeli%20military%20conception%20of%20what%20was%20necessary%20in%20a%20war%20with%20Hamas%20viewed%20disproportionate%20destruction%20and%20creating%20the%20maximum%20disruption%20in%20the%20lives%20of%20many%20people%20as%20a%20legitimate%20means%20to%20achieve%20not%20only%20military%20but%20also%20political%20goals%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20report.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAbout%20two%20years%20later%2C%20the%20chair%20of%20the%20fact-finding%20mission%20claimed%20that%20he%20would%20have%20written%20the%20report%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fopinions%2Freconsidering-the-goldstone-report-on-israel-and-war-crimes%2F2011%2F04%2F01%2FAFg111JC_story.html%3Fhpid%3Dz3%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Edifferently%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20the%20other%20three%20members%20of%20the%20mission%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fcommentisfree%2F2011%2Fapr%2F14%2Fgoldstone-report-statement-un-gaza%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Edisagreed%20strongly%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20stating%20there%20was%20%E2%80%9Cno%20justification%20for%20any%20demand%20or%20expectation%20for%20reconsideration%20of%20the%20report%20as%20nothing%20of%20substance%20has%20appeared%20that%20would%20in%20any%20way%20change%20the%20context%2C%20findings%20or%20conclusions%20of%20that%20report%20with%20respect%20to%20any%20of%20the%20parties%20to%20the%C2%A0Gaza%C2%A0conflict%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697201100000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F13174809%2FGaza-ruin.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fexplained-indiscriminate-targeting-civilians-war-crime-un-experts%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Three%20aspects%20of%20international%20humanitarian%20law%20apply%20apply%20to%20the%20current%20conflict%3A%20the%20protection%20of%20civilians%2C%20the%20right%20to%20self-defence%20and%20the%20rule%20of%20proportionality.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A20%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fexplained-indiscriminate-targeting-civilians-war-crime-un-experts%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Why%20evacuating%20northern%20Gaza%20in%20less%20than%2024%20hours%20is%20'impossible'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697201100000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F10%2F768x432%2Fskynews-gaza-israel-hamas-war_6320262.jpg%3F20231013114148%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fgaza-evacuation-why-getting-people-out-in-less-than-24-hours-is-impossible-12983748%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Evacuating%20more%20than%20a%20million%20people%20from%20northern%20Gaza%20in%20less%20than%2024%20hours%20is%20%26quot%3Bimpossible%26quot%3B%20for%20a%20number%20of%20reasons%2C%20aid%20workers%20have%20told%20Sky%20News.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A642%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fgaza-evacuation-why-getting-people-out-in-less-than-24-hours-is-impossible-12983748%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fgaza-evacuation-why-getting-people-out-in-less-than-24-hours-is-impossible-12983748%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fgaza-evacuation-why-getting-people-out-in-less-than-24-hours-is-impossible-12983748%22%7D%2